<div class='elementListBrownSeparator'></div>
<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1918735-what-inspired-you-to-write-klive-s">What inspired you to write Klive’s character? Is he based on a real person or purely fictional? The way you write his POV is as if you know someone like him, like you’re inside the mind of the criminal. He’s definitely the kind of dark, dastardly villain I could go for. You never know exactly what he’s up to, but you get the vibe that he’s got something deeper, more nefarious going on, yet to be revealed.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1918735'><a id="like_count_community_question_1918735" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1918735?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F54352941-don-t-close-your-eyes">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1918735-what-inspired-you-to-write-klive-s">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1918735-what-inspired-you-to-write-klive-s">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/68287669-lynessa-layne"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1638469534i/68287669._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/68287669-lynessa-layne">Lynessa Layne</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Hi Danielle. Thanks for your question.<br/>I was inspired to write Klive as a means of getting the dangerous romance or dangerous love interest through hum<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Hi Danielle. Thanks for your question.<br />I was inspired to write Klive as a means of getting the dangerous romance or dangerous love interest through human-based flaws because I was tired of only finding that danger and suspenseful conflict in paranormal or supernatural romances. Dangerous people are all around us in our real lives. Some actually have good hearts that come from bad places. I've known many great people who came out of the ashes of ruined lives, including myself, not to say I'm great, but I've found good after bad.<br /><br />Klive starts out a sort of villain and transforms into an antihero. I do pull from reality-based situations to craft my characters. Klive, like Kins and every other character, is a combination of traits in people I've known, but I also fill in the blanks with fiction.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1067918" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1067918&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1918735-what-inspired-you-to-write-klive-s%2Fanswers%2F1067918-hi-danielle-thanks">flag</a>
</div>
